TY  - JOUR
AU  - Landier, Augustin
AU  - Lovo, Stefano
T1  - Socially Responsible Finance: How to Optimize Impact
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae055
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 38
IS  - 4
SP  - 1211
EP  - 1258
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Can a socially responsible fund (SRF) improve social welfare while maximizing assets under management? We consider a two-sector model integrating financial intermediation, emissions’ negative externalities, and investors’ social preferences with regard to value alignment and impact. In scenarios with a high proportion of value-aligned investors, the SRF invests in clean sectors and compels recipients companies to use low-emission suppliers from the polluting sector, which appeals to both investor types. Alternatively, the SRF adopts a dual-fund approach, with one fund targeting clean sectors for value-aligned investors and another focusing on reducing direct emissions in polluting sectors to attract impact investors.
Y2  - 5/12/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae055
ER  - 



